        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3895078921" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15214986501209359897">I always imagined the story of the Phantom of the Opera differently. On the one hand, I thought the story was set in Italy and on the other hand, I always thought it was a love story between the Phantom and Christine. Well, my dear readers, that was wrong. The setting is beautiful Paris, but this beautiful love story is not really a love story. The Phantom takes Christine to the underworld of the opera to win her love. But Christine&apos;s childhood sweetheart tries everything to free her from his gh</span>
  <span id="freeText15214986501209359897" style="display:none">I always imagined the story of the Phantom of the Opera differently. On the one hand, I thought the story was set in Italy and on the other hand, I always thought it was a love story between the Phantom and Christine. Well, my dear readers, that was wrong. The setting is beautiful Paris, but this beautiful love story is not really a love story. The Phantom takes Christine to the underworld of the opera to win her love. But Christine's childhood sweetheart tries everything to free her from his ghosts. There is an eerie feeling throughout the book, which makes it very exciting. But at the end, there are parts that are not very fitting for the story. It took the energy out of the book. However, the ending brings back chills and heartbreak. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15214986501209359897" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


